@startuml route_activity_to_ibox_link_state_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Route Activity To IBOX Link State Signal Flow\n(route activity + boundary/service context -> IBOX link and route state)

participant "Road zone / boundary /\nservice context" as RouteCtx #F4F7FB
participant "IBOX\ninfotainment gateway owner" as IBOX #E8F7E8
participant "IBOX state bus" as LinkBus #FFF4CC
participant "Observers / IVI state" as Obs #E8F0FE

== Route Inputs ==

RouteCtx -> IBOX : roadZone\nboundaryAlive\nwarningPathStatus\nfailSafeMode\nalertLevel
IBOX -> IBOX : routeActive = (roadZone > 0) ? 1 : 0
IBOX -> IBOX : diagStage = ethDiagBoundaryStage(routeActive,...)
IBOX -> IBOX : if diagStage == 1 and vehicle/nav fresh\nthen linkMode elevated
IBOX -> IBOX : routeState derived from routeActive / diagStage / link conditions
note right of IBOX
Representative inputs
- roadZone
- boundaryAlive
- warningPathStatus
- failSafeMode
end note

== Route / Link Publish ==

IBOX -> LinkBus : linkMode / routeState / signalBars / serviceFlags
note right of IBOX
Representative outputs
- linkMode
- routeState
- signalBars
- serviceFlags
end note

== Downstream Visibility ==

LinkBus -> Obs : infotainment connectivity /\nroute-state readback

note over RouteCtx, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. Route activity and boundary context reach IBOX
2. IBOX derives route state and link mode
3. IBOX publishes infotainment route/connectivity status
4. Observers expose the effective link and route posture
end note

@enduml
